# Framework7 + Capacitor + React Development Rules

# 1. Edit your app in `src/` - all development happens here
allow: src/**
allow: public/**
allow: package.json
allow: capacitor.config.json
allow: framework7.json
allow: postcss.config.js
allow: vite.config.js

# Do not edit generated native files directly
deny: ios/**
deny: android/**

# Exception: allow editing native code only for custom plugins or platform-specific fixes
allow: ios/App/App/AppDelegate.swift
allow: android/app/src/main/java/io/framework7/myapp/MainActivity.java

# Do not edit files in www/ (output directory)
deny: www/**

# Development Workflow:
# 1. Edit your app in `src/`
# 2. Then run: npm run build
# 3. (Only if you added plugins or modified native stuff) npx cap sync ios
# 4. Open and run in Xcode: npx cap run ios

note: Development workflow - After editing files in src/, run: 1) npm run build, 2) npx cap copy ios, 3) npx cap sync ios (only if plugins changed), 4) npx cap run ios